HEADWORD: Salian
<hw>Sa"lian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Denoting a tribe of
Franks who established themselves early in the fourth century on the
river Sala [now Yssel]; Salic.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
Salian Frank.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

